swmm_python.Rmd

Prerequisites

Install Anaconda on your computer (requires admin rights!): https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual#Downloads

Or Miniconda with kwb.python::install_miniconda() (no admin rights required).

For this tutorial Miniconda is used.

Install miniconda

kwb.python::install_miniconda()
#> * Downloading 'https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-MacOSX-x86_64.sh' ...
#> * Installing Miniconda -- please wait a moment ...
#> * Miniconda has been successfully installed at '/Users/runner/Library/r-miniconda'.
#> [1] "/Users/runner/Library/r-miniconda"

Install pywmm

pyswmm_v1.0.1

Setup an environment named swmm_py for where we want to install pyswmm v1.0.1

DOES NOT WORK currently!

### Create python environment 

### Use Python 3.8 (as for 3.9 installation of "pyswmm" requires 
### Microsoft Visual Studio 2017: "Building windows wheels for Python 3.9 requires 
### Microsoft Visual Studio 2017 Get it with "Visual Studio 2017§

reticulate::conda_create(envname = "swmm_py", packages = "python=3.8")

################################################################################
### Install "pyswmm" (v1.0.1 available, status:2021-01-25)
### https://pypi.org/project/pyswmm/ 
################################################################################
reticulate::use_miniconda(condaenv = "swmm_py", required = TRUE)

pyconfig <- reticulate::py_config()

reticulate::use_python(python = pyconfig$python, required = TRUE)

## on windows: (try this: https://github.com/rstudio/reticulate/issues/367#issuecomment-432920802)
if(.Platform$OS.type == "windows") {
  Sys.setenv(PATH= paste(PATH = pyconfig$pythonpath, 
                         Sys.getenv()["PATH"], sep=";")
  )
 # Sys.setenv(RETICULATE_PYTHON = pyconfig$python)
}

reticulate::py_install(packages = "pyswmm", 
                       envname = "swmm_py", 
                       pip = TRUE, 
                       pip_ignore_installed = TRUE)

### Downgrade dependency "aenum" to get rid of error: 
### reticulate::import("pyswmm") 
### Error in py_module_import(module, convert = convert) : 
### NameError: name 'US' is not defined
### https://github.com/OpenWaterAnalytics/pyswmm/issues/272#issuecomment-782697886
### should be fixed in next release of "swmm-toolkit" (v0.9.0)
### https://github.com/OpenWaterAnalytics/swmm-python/pull/67

reticulate::conda_install(envname = "swmm_py", 
                          packages = "aenum=2.2.6")

# indicate that we want to use a specific condaenv
reticulate::use_miniconda(condaenv = "swmm_py", required = TRUE)

reticulate::py_config()

pyswmm <- reticulate::import("pyswmm", convert = TRUE)
#Fehler in py_module_import(module, convert = convert) : 
# ImportError: DLL load failed while importing _solver: 
# The entered module was not found.

### check pyswmm version (should be v1.0.1 as installed using "pip") 
#pyswmm$VERSION_INFO

pyswmm_v0.6.2

Setup an environment named swmm_conda for where we want to install pyswmm v0.6.2

################################################################################
### Install "pyswmm" (v0.6.2 available, status:2021-01-25)
### https://pypi.org/project/pyswmm/ 
################################################################################

reticulate::conda_create("swmm_conda", packages = c("python=3.8", "pyswmm"))
#> [1] "/Users/runner/Library/r-miniconda/envs/swmm_conda/bin/python"

reticulate::use_miniconda(condaenv = "swmm_conda", required = TRUE)

pyconfig <- reticulate::py_config()

## on windows: (try this: https://github.com/rstudio/reticulate/issues/367#issuecomment-432920802)
if(.Platform$OS.type == "windows") {
  Sys.setenv(PATH= paste(PATH = pyconfig$pythonpath, 
                         Sys.getenv()["PATH"], sep=";")
  )
  #Sys.setenv(RETICULATE_PYTHON = pyconfig$python)
}

reticulate::use_python(python = pyconfig$python, required = TRUE)

pyswmm <- reticulate::import("pyswmm")
### check pyswmm version (should be v0.6.2 as installed using "conda") 
pyswmm$VERSION_INFO
#> [[1]]
#> [1] 0
#> 
#> [[2]]
#> [1] 6
#> 
#> [[3]]
#> [1] 2

path_swmm_inp <- kwb.swmm::extdata_file("models/green-roof_neubrandenburg/neubrand.inp")


withr::with_dir(new = dirname(path_swmm_inp), 
                code = {
sim <- pyswmm$Simulation(inputfile = basename(path_swmm_inp),
                         reportfile = "neubrand.rpt",
                         outputfile = "neubrand.out")
                  }
)

sim$engine_version
#> 5.3.0.dev0
sim$system_units
#> [1] "SI"
sim$flow_units
#> [1] "LPS"
sim$engine_version
#> 5.3.0.dev0
sim$execute()
sim$runoff_error
#> [1] 0

swmm_lib <- "C:/_UserProg/EPA SWMM 5.1.015/swmm5.dll"
if(file.exists(swmm_lib)) {
 
 pyswmm$lib$use(swmm_lib)
 
withr::with_dir(new = dirname(path_swmm_inp), 
                code = {
sim <- pyswmm$Simulation(inputfile = basename(path_swmm_inp),
                         reportfile = "neubrand.rpt",
                         outputfile = "neubrand.out")
                  }
)

}
